{{Quote|Advantage #7: Blast Proof. The LIN Demolitionmech is One Tough Droid.|Excerpt from the advertising campaign for LIN Demolitionmechs|<ref name="The New Essential Guide to Droids">''[[The New Essential Guide to Droids]]''</ref>}}
'''''Blast Proof''''' was the title of advertisement made by [[Schaum/Yfarg/Welbig/Fabrico and Associates|SchaumAssoc]] for [[Cybot Galactica/Legends|Cybot Galactica's]] [[LIN demolitionmech autonomous minelayer/Legends|LIN Demolitionmech]] line of [[Droid/Legends|droids]] as part of their advertising campaign. In the advertisement, several demolitionmech were floating free in space while being fired at by the [[Turbolaser/Legends|turbolaser]] of a battleship. Despite the heavy amount of fire, the droids, which had been knocked around violently due to the laser bolts, emerged intact without a scratch. Numerous customers actually decided to test the blast-proof quality of their demolitionmechs by exposing them to [[Blaster/Legends|blaster]] fire. In real life, the droids were obviously not blast proof, and Cybot Galactica received numerous inquiries and even more complaints from their customers. Initially, Cybot Galactica pointed out to complaining customers that it was merely a "clear comic exaggeration," but eventually they decided to pull the ad altogether.

